claim.claim-text:
1. A mechanical motion amplifier for amplification of an amplitude of a motion from an actuator unit, comprising:
at least two beams connected in a series at an angle, each beam having a thickness substantially smaller than its orthogonal expansion;
wherein each beam in turn comprises at least one supporting element about which said beam is pivotable;
wherein, when said serial connection is exposed to a pushing or pulling motion having a first amplitude from at least one actuator unit, the actuator unit transferring motion to a first beam of the at least two beams through a segment disposed at an angle to a direction along the length of the first beam, the motion is amplified and a second, substantially parallel motion is generated having a second amplitude larger than said first amplitude; and
wherein said amplified second amplitude and its direction is obtained from a transmission of a construction dependent on how said beams, said supporting elements, and said at least one actuator unit are positioned in relation to each other.
